To run tests, execute from Julia

> include("runtests.jl")
> run_multistart()

The results are stored in the 'RESULTS' file.

Please ensure that all required packages are installed in your Julia, including
MDGP (https://github.com/leonardosecchin/MDGP.git).

Tests can be ran in parallel. To do this, starts Julia specifying the number of
threads: julia -t [NUMBER OF THREADS]

Instances were generated using the PDB parser (pdb_parser.py) created by Wagner
da Rocha. For more information and updates, visit Wagner's Github page
https://github.com/wdarocha/pdb-parser.

You can regenerate the instances by running the script parse_from_PDB.sh in the
'dataset' folder. Note, however, that the new generated instances may differ
from the original ones, as the parser employ pseudorandom numbers.